Package: openfollow
Version: @VERSION@
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: Paul Hermann, Michel Honold, Vinzenz Schultz <hello@openfollow.app>
Homepage: https://openfollow.app
Section: video
Priority: optional
Depends: @PYTHON_DEP@, python3-gi, python3-gi-cairo,
 gir1.2-gstreamer-1.0, gir1.2-gst-plugins-base-1.0, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, gir1.2-rsvg-2.0,
 libgstreamer1.0-0, gstreamer1.0-plugins-base, gstreamer1.0-plugins-good,
 gstreamer1.0-plugins-bad, gstreamer1.0-libav, gstreamer1.0-libcamera, gstreamer1.0-gtk3,
 gstreamer1.0-tools, libglfw3, @ALSA_DEP@, cage, seatd, kanshi, librsvg2-bin,
 adwaita-icon-theme, adduser
Recommends: gir1.2-webkit2-4.1
Description: Live video stage-tracking with 3D position output for show control
 OpenFollow tracks people and objects in 3D from a video feed and a gamepad,
 turning an operator's aim into real-time position data that automates
 lighting, audio and media.
 .
 It emits PosiStageNet (PSN), Object Transform Protocol (OTP), Open Sound
 Control (OSC) and Real-Time Tracking Protocol (RTTrPM), and runs as a
 self-contained Wayland kiosk on Raspberry Pi with an on-device web UI.
 .
 This package bundles the OpenFollow runtime together with all of its Python
 dependencies in a private virtualenv under /opt/openfollow, so it installs
 and runs without internet access.
